ners.   </p><p>D&rsquo;Andrea and his team created the Flying Machine Arena to test the gravity-defying abilities of their athletic flying robots. Building on research in the Flying Machine Arena, ETH Z&uuml;rich partnered with its spin-off company Verity Studios and with Cirque du Soleil to create &ldquo;<a href=\"http://raffaello.name/projects/sparked/\" target=\"_blank\">Sparked</a>,&rdquo; a short film showcasing the unexpected airborne dexterity of quadcopters.  D&rsquo;Andrea is the co-founder of Kiva Systems, a robotics company that develops intelligent automated warehouse systems and that was acquired by Amazon in 2012.</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Raffaello D'Andrea","tags":["beauty","creativity","demo","drones","design","future","invention","technology","flight"],"title":"Meet the dazzling flying machines of the future","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":3267530}]}
